    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Shock Waves From the Mideast, on Two Fronts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Avi Jacobs letter says attack on USS Cole gives Americans inkling of terror that Israelis live with daily (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While I grieve for the families of American sailors killed, wounded or missing after the tragic bombing of the Navy destroyer Cole in Yemen (front page, Oct. 13), a horrible double standard still exists.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While I grieve for the families of American sailors killed, wounded or missing after the tragic bombing of the Navy destroyer Cole in Yemen (front page, Oct. 13), a horrible double standard still exists.</p>
        <p>While President Clinton appropriately announces that ''we will find out who was responsible and hold them accountable,'' the Israelis are not only urged by Secretary of State Madeleine K. Albright ''to bring an immediate end to the current operations'' against the Palestinians but are also condemned by the Security Council.</p>
        <p>Sadly, Americans now have an inkling of the terror that Israelis live with daily: surrounded by Arabs who want nothing more than to end the Jewish presence in Israel.</p>
        <p>It is to be hoped that an end can be put to terrorism aimed against American and Israeli citizens alike.</p>
        <p>AVI JACOBS  Baltimore, Oct. 13, 2000</p>
      </block>
